  <header class="header">
    <div class="header-eyebrow">Architecture Reference</div>
    <h1>Agentic ERP Pipeline →<br><span>Medallion / Data Vault / Data Mesh</span></h1>
    <p class="header-sub">
      Mapping our AI-native fund administration engine to industry-standard data architecture terminology.
      These are not competing patterns — they solve different problems at different layers, and we use them together.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- ═══ KEY INSIGHT ═══ -->

  <div class="insight-box">
    <h3>The Point</h3>
    <p>
      <strong>Medallion</strong> is our data layering pattern (Bronze → Silver → Gold).
      <strong>Data Vault</strong> is our modelling discipline (Hubs, Satellites, Links for auditability and history).
      <strong>Data Mesh</strong> describes how domain ownership is distributed.
      <strong>The Agentic Pipeline</strong> is the processing engine that moves data through these layers — with LLMs generating code, deterministic systems verifying it, and humans approving exceptions.
      These four concepts are complementary, not competing.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ SECTION 1: MEDALLION MAPPING ═══ -->

  <div class="section" style="animation-delay: 0.1s;">
    <div class="section-label">Section 01</div>
    <h2>Medallion Layer Mapping</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">
      The 5-step agentic pipeline maps directly onto the Bronze → Silver → Gold medallion pattern.
      Each layer progressively increases data quality, trust, and business readiness.
    </p>

```
<div class="medallion-flow">
  <!-- BRONZE -->
  <div class="medallion-layer bronze">
    <div class="layer-badge">Bronze Layer</div>
    <div class="layer-title">Raw Ingestion</div>
    <div class="layer-subtitle">Accept anything, transform nothing</div>
    <ul class="layer-agents">
      <li>
        <span class="agent-tag tag-det">DET</span>
        <strong>A1: Intake Agent</strong> — Routes inbound documents (PDFs, emails, CSVs, API feeds) by type. Classifies without transforming.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="agent-tag tag-llm">LLM</span>
        <strong>A2: Reader Agent</strong> — Extracts structured JSON from raw documents. Per-field confidence scores attached. Schema-on-read, not schema-on-write.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>

  <!-- SILVER -->
  <div class="medallion-layer silver">
    <div class="layer-badge">Silver Layer</div>
    <div class="layer-title">Validated &amp; Verified</div>
    <div class="layer-subtitle">Generate, execute, verify, flag</div>
    <ul class="layer-agents">
      <li>
        <span class="agent-tag tag-llm">LLM</span>
        <strong>A3: Builder Agent</strong> — Generates Python calculation scripts. Checks Tool Library first. Writes code, never computes.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="agent-tag tag-llm">LLM</span>
        <strong>A3b: Builder (Secondary)</strong> — Independent code generation using a different model family. Dual-builder consensus.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="agent-tag tag-det">DET</span>
        <strong>A4: Constitution Agent</strong> — Executes code in sandbox. 4 guardrails: double-entry, LPA limits, ACID, dimensional integrity.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="agent-tag tag-det">DET</span>
        <strong>Z3 Formal Verification</strong> — Proves arithmetic properties hold for all inputs, not just test cases.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="agent-tag tag-ml">ML</span>
        <strong>A5: Anomaly Agent</strong> — Isolation Forest + EWMA + PELT. Flags statistical outliers, low confidence, material events.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>

  <!-- GOLD -->
  <div class="medallion-layer gold">
    <div class="layer-badge">Gold Layer</div>
    <div class="layer-title">Production-Ready</div>
    <div class="layer-subtitle">Approved, posted, audit-trailed</div>
    <ul class="layer-agents">
      <li>
        <span class="agent-tag tag-human">HUMAN</span>
        <strong>A7: Human Gate</strong> — Expert reviews flagged items only. Approves → Tool Library. ~85%+ auto-posted.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="agent-tag tag-llm">LLM</span>
        <strong>A6: Auditor Agent</strong> — Generates plain-English explanation of the code for human reviewers. Cross-refs Fund Rules Ontology.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="agent-tag tag-det">DET</span>
        <strong>A8: Posting Agent</strong> — Atomic posting to production ledger. Full audit trail. Client portal update.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div style="margin-top: 16px; padding: 16px 20px; background: var(--surface); border-radius: 4px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary);">
  <strong style="color: var(--text);">Key distinction:</strong> In a standard Medallion implementation, each layer is a passive data store.
  In our architecture, each layer is an <em>active processing stage</em> — agents perform work, not just transformations.
  The Medallion pattern describes <em>where</em> data lives at each stage of trust. The agents describe <em>how</em> it gets there.
</div>
```

