  <div class="section" style="animation-delay: 0.2s;">
    <div class="section-label">Section 02</div>
    <h2>Data Vault Modelling Layer</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">
      Underneath the Medallion layers, our entity model follows Data Vault 2.0 principles.
      This gives us full auditability, change history, and the ability to absorb data from any source without schema conflicts.
    </p>

```
<div class="vault-grid">
  <div class="vault-card">
    <div class="vault-icon">🏛️</div>
    <div class="vault-label">Hubs</div>
    <div class="vault-title">Business Keys</div>
    <div class="vault-desc">
      Core entities identified by durable business keys. LEI codes where available, synthetic canonical IDs where not.
      Hubs never change — they are append-only records of entity existence.
    </div>
    <div class="vault-example">
      HUB_FUND (fund_id, LEI)<br>
      HUB_INVESTOR (investor_id, LEI)<br>
      HUB_COUNTERPARTY (entity_id, canonical_id)
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="vault-card">
    <div class="vault-icon">🛰️</div>
    <div class="vault-label">Satellites</div>
    <div class="vault-title">Change History</div>
    <div class="vault-desc">
      Temporal attributes attached to hubs. Every change creates a new satellite record — never overwrites.
      This is how we answer "what did we know, and when did we know it?" for any regulatory query.
    </div>
    <div class="vault-example">
      SAT_FUND_NAV (nav_date, nav_per_share, aum)<br>
      SAT_INVESTOR_KYC (kyc_status, risk_rating, review_date)<br>
      SAT_FUND_FEES (mgmt_rate, perf_rate, effective_from)
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="vault-card">
    <div class="vault-icon">🔗</div>
    <div class="vault-label">Links</div>
    <div class="vault-title">Relationships</div>
    <div class="vault-desc">
      Many-to-many relationships between hubs. An investor can hold multiple funds; a fund can have multiple administrators; a counterparty can serve multiple roles.
    </div>
    <div class="vault-example">
      LNK_FUND_INVESTOR (fund_id, investor_id)<br>
      LNK_TRADE_COUNTERPARTY (trade_id, cp_id)<br>
      LNK_FUND_SERVICE_PROVIDER (fund_id, provider_id)
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div style="padding: 16px 20px; background: var(--surface); border-radius: 4px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary);">
  <strong style="color: var(--text);">Entity Resolution connection:</strong> Our two-pass entity resolution pipeline (deterministic LEI matching → LLM fuzzy matching → HITL review) feeds directly into Hub creation.
  When 10 messy backend systems call the same counterparty by different names, the resolution engine produces a single canonical Hub record with provenance tracking in the Satellites.
</div>
```

