      The Tool Library is itself a data product — verified, versioned, reusable calculation templates.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="mesh-card">
    <div class="mesh-principle">Principle 3</div>
    <h4>Self-Serve Platform</h4>
    <p>
      The Agentic Pipeline is the self-serve infrastructure. Domain teams don't build ETL — they upload documents and describe what they need. The pipeline handles ingestion, transformation, and verification.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="mesh-card">
    <div class="mesh-principle">Principle 4</div>
    <h4>Federated Governance</h4>
    <p>
      The Constitution Agent enforces global standards (double-entry, ACID, dimensional integrity) while domain-specific rules live in the Fund Rules Ontology. Central guardrails, local logic.
    </p>
  </div>
