    <h2>The HOW — Not Just the What</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">
      The questions that separate real architecture from three-box diagrams — and how we answer them.
    </p>

```
<table class="comp-table">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Architecture Question</th>
      <th>Industry Pattern</th>
      <th>Our Implementation</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Conflicting business keys?</td>
      <td>Data Vault Hubs + business key resolution</td>
      <td>Two-pass entity resolution: deterministic LEI matching, then LLM fuzzy matching with HITL review queue. Canonical IDs assigned at Hub level.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Change history?</td>
      <td>Data Vault Satellites (temporal versioning)</td>
      <td>Every attribute change appends a new Satellite record. Full bitemporal tracking: when it happened vs. when we recorded it. Regulatory queries answered from Satellite history.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Transformation consistency?</td>
      <td>dbt-style lineage + testing</td>
      <td>Six defence layers: Dual-Builder consensus, Tool Library regression, Z3 formal verification, Inverse Verification, 1000+ property tests, Human Gate for novelty. No equivalent in standard data pipelines.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Key management?</td>
      <td>Surrogate keys + natural key mapping</td>
      <td>LEI as the golden natural key where available. Canonical surrogate IDs from entity resolution where not. Hub records are append-only — no key conflicts possible.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Schema evolution?</td>
      <td>Schema-on-read at Bronze, enforce at Silver</td>
      <td>Reader Agent accepts any format on any day. Data Dictionary normalises at extraction time. New fields absorbed without pipeline changes. "Never ask upstream to change."</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Quality assurance?</td>
      <td>Great Expectations / dbt tests</td>
      <td>Constitution Agent runs 4 guardrails per transaction. Anomaly Agent applies statistical triage (Isolation Forest, EWMA, PELT). Zero manual data quality rules to maintain — the agents learn from approvals.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
```

